Methodology

Essential Workers Metric

The data used to assess the % of workers deemed essential was determined using the Labor Market Information (LMI) Institutes Standard Occupation Classification (SOC) codes connectd to essential businesses. (https://www.lmiontheweb.org/more-than-half-of-u-s-workers-in-critical-occupations-in-the-fight-against-covid-19/). The SOC codes the LMI institute provided are based on the Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agencys list from April 17, 2020 (https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/publications/Version_3.0_CISA_Guidance_on_Essential_Critical_Infrastructure_Workers_4.pdf). These codes have the advantage of being directly linked to census respondees so that each respondee has one SOC code.

sj_tracts <- 
  scc_tracts %>% 
  st_centroid() %>% 
  st_set_geometry(NULL) %>% 
  left_join(scc_tracts%>% dplyr::select(GEOID), by = "GEOID") %>% 
  st_as_sf() %>% 
  rename(tractgroup = "GEOID") %>% 
  select(tractgroup,geometry)

SOC Essential Code Dataset

data_dir <- "/Users/spencerrobinson/Documents/covid19/Spencer_Robinson/"
soc <- readxl::read_xlsx(str_c(data_dir,"SOC-Codes-CISA-Critical-Infrastructure-Workers-with-OES-Data.xlsx"))
soc <- soc %>% 
  mutate(Critical = replace_na(Critical, FALSE)) %>% 
  mutate(Critical = replace(Critical, Critical == "X",TRUE)) %>% 
  fill(`Major Group Description`) %>% 
  group_by(`Major Group Description`,Critical) %>%#Group by Major Group Description - as this is the only thing we have data for
  summarize(count = n()) %>% 
  spread(Critical, count) %>% 
  rename(c("essential" = "TRUE", "nonessential" = "FALSE")) %>% 
  mutate(essential = replace_na(essential, 0)) %>% 
  mutate(total = essential+nonessential, fracSOC = essential/total) %>%  #We weight each category by number of essential occupations in each occupation description
  select(`Major Group Description`, fracSOC)

occupation <-
  getCensus(
    name = "acs/acs5",
    vintage = 2018,
    region = "tract:*", 
    regionin = "state:06+county:085",
    vars = "group(B24011)"
  )%>%
  as_tibble() %>% 
  mutate(
    tractgroup = paste0(state,county,tract)
  ) %>% 
  select_if(!names(.) %in% c("GEO_ID","state","county","tract","NAME")) %>% 
  dplyr::select(-c(contains("EA"),contains("MA"),contains("M"))) %>% 
  dplyr::select(-c(contains("001"),contains("002"),contains("003"),contains("006"), contains("010"),contains("016"),contains("017"), contains("018"), contains("021"), contains("022"), contains("026"),contains("029"), contains("033"))) %>% 
  rename(
    "Management Occupations" = B24011_004E,
    "Business and Financial Operations Occupations" = B24011_005E,
    "Computer and Mathematical Occupations" = B24011_007E,
    "Architecture and Engineering Occupations" = B24011_008E,
    "Life, Physical, and Social Science Occupations" = B24011_009E,
    "Community and Social Service Occupations" = B24011_011E,
    "Legal Occupations" = B24011_012E,

    "Arts, Design, Entertainment, Sports, and Media Occupations" = B24011_014E,
    "Healthcare Practitioners and Technical Occupations"= B24011_015E,
    "Healthcare Support Occupations" = B24011_019E,
    "Protective Service Occupations" = B24011_020E,
    "Food Preparation and Serving Related Occupations" = B24011_023E,
    "Building and Grounds Cleaning and Maintenance Occupations" = B24011_024E,
    "Personal Care and Service Occupations" = B24011_025E,
    "Sales and Related Occupations" = B24011_027E,
    "Office and Administrative Support Occupations" = B24011_028E,
    "Farming, Fishing, and Forestry Occupations" = B24011_030E,
    "Construction and Extraction Occupations" = B24011_031E,
    "Installation, Maintenance, and Repair Occupations" = B24011_032E,

  ) %>%

Join occupation and CISA dataframe

occupation_essential_tract <- occupation%>%  
  left_join(soc, by = c("SOC" = "Major Group Description")) %>% 
  mutate(essWorkers = workers*fracSOC) %>%
  group_by(tractgroup) %>% 
  summarize(workers = sum(workers), essWorkers = sum(essWorkers)) %>% 
  mutate(fracEssential = essWorkers/workers)

essential_workers_visualize <- ggplot(data = occupation_essential_tract, aes(x = fracEssential))+
  geom_histogram()+
  labs(y = "Number of Tract Groups", x = "% Essential Workers")+
  ggtitle("Distribution of Block Group Essential Worker Data Method 2")

essential_workers_visualize

Time to map!

blue_pal <- colorNumeric(
  palette = "Blues",
  domain = 
    c(occupation_essential_tract %>% 
        pull(fracEssential) %>% 
        unique())
)

sj_essential_map <- leaflet(data = occupation_essential_tract) %>% 
  addProviderTiles(providers$CartoDB.Positron) %>% 
  addPolygons(
    data = 
      occupation_essential_tract %>% 
      left_join(sj_tracts) %>%
      st_as_sf() %>% st_set_crs(4326),
    fillColor = ~blue_pal(fracEssential),
    color = "white",
    weight = 0.25,
    fillOpacity = 0.5,
    label = ~paste0(fracEssential,"%"),
    highlightOptions = highlightOptions(
      weight = 2,
      opacity = 1
    )
  ) %>% 
  addLegend(pal = blue_pal, values = ~fracEssential, opacity = 1, title = "% Workers in Essential Occupations")
